"A total of 7.5 to 15 cm of rain is expected from Baja California to northwestern Sonora, with a risk of up to 25 cm", reported weather.com.
Rosa will then travel north across Mexico as a tropical storm and reach Arizona’s border early Tuesday morning as a tropical low pressure, which will then travel through Arizona and into southern Utah late Tuesday night.
"The greatest danger from Rosa and its remaining energy is very heavy rain in Baja California, northwestern Sonora and the desert in the southwestern United States," said the National Hurricane Center.
